In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Prep ==

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary; halve crosswise.

== Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @ponzu sauce{12%ml}, @umami ginger sauce{4%tablespoon}, half the @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 2 TBSP water, and 1/4 tsp @sugar{1/4%tsp} (all the vinegar, 4 TBSP water, and 1/2 tsp sugar for 4 servings).

Stir in @sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste.

== Stir-Fry ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}; season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{to taste}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces, then stir in green beans. Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until pork is cooked through and green beans are browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir ponzu mixture into pan with pork and green beans. Cook, stirring often, until slightly thickened, ~{1%minute} more.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Divide rice between #bowls{2}. Top with pork and green bean stir-fry; garnish with @wonton strips{1%cup}. Drizzle with @spicy mayo{4%tablespoon} and any remaining Sriracha to taste. Serve.

> Ground Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.